@hviews@n displays a graphics image file.
Supported formats include:
@e.koa @n C64 Koala
@e.iff @n Amiga IFF ILBM
@e.lbm @n Amiga IFF ILBM
@e.pcx @n PCX
@e.bmp @n Windows Bitmap
@e.bmx @n X16 BMX
@e.dd  @n C64 Doodle
@e.ddl @n C64 Doodle

@eSYNTAX:  @n view @pfilename

Press any key to exit the viewer.
Press '@hb@n' to save the current image as X16 BMX format.

Color cycling is supported on certain image format such as IFF.
If you want to exit from viewing such an image, you have to stop the color cycling effect first. This is done by pressing the '@hSTOP@n' key.
You can exit the viewer normally by pressing any other key after that.
